cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper deals with statistical models for extracting specific shapes from 3D surface data, with a focus on the human face. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the statistical and computational aspects of the models, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the use of databases and learning from examples suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
